.TH "funzy_getrom" "1" "2026-06-09" "" "funzyto770 User Manuals"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
funzy_getrom - extract the Thomson TO7 high ROM from a tape file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]funzy_getrom\f[R] \f[I]file.k7\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]funzy_getrom\f[R] reads a Thomson TO7 or TO7-70 cassette tape file
(.k7 format) and extracts the high ROM image from it, writing a
6144-byte .rom file.
.PP
The ROM must have been previously saved on the TO7 or TO7-70 computer
using the following BASIC command:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
SAVEM\[dq]ROM\[dq],&HE800,&HFFFF,0
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
The output file takes the name of the input file with the \f[B].k7\f[R]
extension replaced by \f[B].rom\f[R].
.PP
The TO7 high ROM covers 6144 bytes (address range 0xE800\[en]0xFFFF) and
is required to run the \f[B]funzyto770\f[R] emulator.
The resulting .rom file must be renamed \f[B]romto770\f[R] and placed in
the emulator\[cq]s working directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
This program accepts no options.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]file.k7\f[R]
Input cassette tape file.
.TP
\f[I]file.rom\f[R]
Output ROM image (6144 bytes), named after the input file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Extract the TO7 ROM from a tape recording:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
funzy_getrom romto770.k7
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Then rename the output for use with the emulator:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
mv romto770.rom romto770
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]funzy_getmemo7\f[R](1), \f[B]funzy_wav2k7\f[R](1)
.SH BUGS
.PP
No known bugs.
